25 LC 112 3554
Senate Resolution 498
By: Senators Wicks of the 34th and Davenport of the 17th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending the North Fayette Community Association; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the North Fayette Community Association (NFCA) was founded in August
4 2001 by local homeowners to address shared issues, interests, and concerns affecting the
5 North Fayette community and was officially chartered as a non-profit, non-partisan
6 organization in October 2001; and
7 WHEREAS, the NFCA was born out of a collective sense of under-representation at the
8 county level and limited access to support, services, resources, and amenities, inspiring
9 residents to organize for change; and
10 WHEREAS, the NFCA has since successfully defended the community from inappropriate
11 developments such as the construction of a service station at the intersection of Highways
12 279 and 314, which would have posed serious challenges to the community; and
13 WHEREAS, in 2009, then-NFCA President Johnnie E. Jones Jr. led a major effort to correct
14 unfair taxation practices that resulted in residents paying taxes to both Clayton and Fulton
