15 counties on large purchases, ultimately securing a zip code reassignment to the Fayetteville
16 Postal System and increasing tax revenue for Fayette County; and
17 WHEREAS, the boundaries of North Fayette span from north of Georgia Highway 54 to
18 Highway 138, east of Highway 74, and west of Highway 85, forming a vital region that has
19 grown from 31,256 residents in 2000 to more than three times that number today; and
20 WHEREAS, North Fayette is home to many active and vibrant subdivisions, including
21 Country Lake, Briarfield, Greer Woods, Westbridge I and II, Northridge, Princeton Chase,
22 Providence, Hampstead Heath, Dix-Lee-On, Newton Plantation, and homes along Highways
23 279 and 314; and
24 WHEREAS, under the leadership of President Bobby Ferrell, the NFCA remains steadfast
25 in its mission to ensure safe neighborhoods, support schools, prevent crime, preserve
26 property values, and promote a high quality of life within North Fayette.
27 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
28 recognize and commend the North Fayette Community Association for its unwavering
29 dedication to community advocacy as well as extend best wishes for continued success in all
30 future endeavors.
31 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
32 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the North Fayette
33 Community Association.
